HEADWORD: nonpartisan
<hw>nonpartisan</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>free from party
affiliation or bias. Opposite of <ant>partisan</ant>.</def> [Narrower
terms: <stype>bipartisan, bipartizan, two-party, two-way</stype>;
<stype>independent </stype>] [Narrower terms: <stype>nonparty, non-party
</stype>]⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> nonpartizan.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>not affiliated with any one party; <as>as, a
<ex>nonpartisan</ex> commission to study crime</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>nonpartisanship</ent>⟦br⟧
